snippet.title: Motherboard
snippet.description:
The future is wonderful, the future is terrifying. We should know, we live there. Whether on the ground or on the web, Motherboard travels the world to uncover the tech and science stories that define what's coming next for this quickly-evolving planet of ours.

Motherboard is a multi-platform, multimedia publication, relying on longform reporting, in-depth blogging, and video and film production to ensure every story is presented in its most gripping and relatable format. Beyond that, we are dedicated to bringing our audience honest portraits of the futures we face, so you can be better informed in your decision-making today.

snippet.title: The Practical Engineer
snippet.description:
Mijn hele leven vraag ik mij al af hoe de dingen om mij heen werken. Als klein kind vond ik het geweldig om oude apparaten open te schroeven en alle componenten er uit te halen. 
Mijn tools hierbij waren een hamer en schroevendraaiers, het meeste ging dan ook nooit meer in elkaar.

Later tijdens mijn studie Luchtvaarttechnologie werd er van mij verwacht dat ik uit een boek kon leren hoe je dingen ontwerpt..
Al vrij snel had ik door dat dat niet de manier is voor mij. Dit is het moment dat ik echt begon met dingen maken. In mijn studentenkamer op de vloer en met wat gereedschap op mijn studie begon ik aan een van mijn eerste projecten: een gyro watch winder.
Sindsdien heb ik altijd een of meerdere projecten waar ik mee bezig ben en probeer ik op deze manier mijn skillset project voor project te groeien.

Op dit kanaal deel ik mijn engineering experimenten, bouw ik gave machines en help ik jou je werkplaats op te bouwen en de maker te worden die jij wil zijn!

snippet.title: Yvan Jacques
snippet.description:
About my channel: 
          (français plus bas)
My movies are spontaneous interpretations of well-known songs, mostly jazz standards. I play both guitar & piano but not in the same time LOL ! 
The song selection and the spontaneous approach reflect my perspective towards playing live night after night, just as I did for a living for about 40 years.

Mes vidéos sont fait spontanément il n'y a pas d'arrangement travaillés pendant des heures,  je joue la pièce avec des moments heureux et d'autres moins. Noté : je joue la guitare et le piano mais pas en même temps LOL

J'ai prévilégiés une approche de musiciens de carrière qui doit jouer les morceaux avec des musiciens différents et dans toutes circonstances. 

Une certaine lecture musical est nécessaire mais pas toujours si  il y a un instrument qui joue la mélodie une bonne connaissance des symboles d'accord s'impose mais surtout l'improvisation est primordial.

snippet.title: Mike Tompkins
snippet.description:
Hey I'm a Music & Video Creator!

I'm so grateful for every single one of you who watches, likes, or shares my videos - as long as you keep doing that, I'll keep making vids! I do my best to read your comments so please keep doing THAT!

Some FAQs
- Can I Use Your Song In A Video?
I have no problem with you using any of my recorded songs in your videos - sometimes the publisher of the original song doesn't allow it however you will find out once you upload the video. So in most cases I would LOVE for you to include my music in your videos but just so you know YouTube's claiming system will probably claim the Sound Recording under my name and I will claim the sound recording part.

- Do You Have The Instrumentals To Your Original Songs?
Yeah! I usually make them available at a certain tier on Patreon.com/MikeTompkins 

- Do You Have The Sheet Music To Your Arrangements?
No, I don't read sheet music thus I don't write it.

snippet.title: Black Lotus
snippet.description: Black Lotus got its start on the Vine app as simply an account to share animated music videos or AMVs, however, in time, it grew into a channel to share thriving underground artists. Black Lotus’ founder, Kyle Arnold, got his start on youtube as a primary contributor and artistic mind behind the AnimeVibe youtube channel, which he eventually left to work on the Black Lotus channel. While it began as a small hobby, over the years, Black Lotus has evolved into a passion project with deep roots in youth and urban culture. Black Lotus places a deep emphasis on the pursuit and perfection of artistry, including but no limited to, photography, photo and video editing, animation, and music. Black Lotus’ main focus is on the curation of content and to act as a social network for artists of all crafts and backgrounds.
